snippet.title: Praying For America (Barron Trump Singing Imagined)
snippet.description:
Praying For America

Check us out on Spotify! https://open.spotify.com/album/3y1CZVxPBVqYl2ljdNVWno?si=lLRWLYbeQcuXD9TQDeKi7A

⬇️⬇️⬇️ Watch more videos below! ⬇️⬇️⬇️
https://youtu.be/WBHJZs8ZeFQ
https://youtu.be/GAdihLnAiXk
https://youtu.be/SZZW8YMZlMg?si=kP7ZE5s5fhhjjpX2
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hq_JjAodbY0

Lyrics:
Verse 1:
I see a nation torn in two,
Divided hearts, a broken view.
We've lost our way, we've lost our sight,
But I know faith can bring back light.

Chorus:
I'm praying for America, down on my knees,
Asking the Lord to hear our pleas.
Through every trial, through every storm,
Only through Him can we be reborn.

Verse 2:
We've turned from truth, we've turned from grace,
Forgotten love, forgotten faith.
But there's still hope, it’s not too late,
If we return, He'll heal this place.

Chorus:
I'm praying for America, down on my knees,
Asking the Lord to hear our pleas.
Through every trial, through every storm,
Only through Him can we be reborn.

Bridge:
Let the churches rise, let the people sing,
Let the bells of freedom ring.
If we stand as one, if we seek His face,
He will bless this land with grace.

Final Chorus:
I'm praying for America, lifting my hands,
Trusting His love to heal this land.
Through every trial, through every storm,
Only through Him can we be reborn.

Outro:
So let us turn, let us believe,
With faith in God, we will not grieve.
I'm praying for America, day and night,
And through His love, we'll win this fight.
